Estimate the Individual Treatment Effect using Poisson Regression

Source: R/estimate_ite_poisson.R
estimate_ite_poisson.Rd

Estimates the Individual Treatment Effect using Poisson Regression given a response vector, a treatment vector, and a features matrix.

Usage

estimate_ite_poisson(y, z, X, X_names, include_offset, offset_name)

Arguments

y

the observed response vector

z

the treatment vector

X

the features matrix

X_names

the names of the covariates

include_offset

whether or not to include an offset when estimating the ITE, for poisson only

offset_name

the name of the offset, if it is to be included

Value

a vector of ITE estimates

Examples

dataset <- generate_cre_dataset(n = 1000, rho = 0, n_rules = 2, p = 10,
